New Records: Glenn Maxwell scored the fastest century in World Cups
Bas de Leede delivered the most expensive over in men's ODI history
Key Match Events: David Warner scored 104, Marnus Labuschagne 62, Glenn Maxwell 106 from just 44 deliveries
Glenn Maxwell's second World Cup century and third overall
Australia won by 309 runs, the largest margin in men's ODI World Cup history
Post-Match Reflections: David Warner expressed pride in the team's resilience after a close win
Scott Edwards, Netherlands captain, cut a forlorn figure at the other end
Miscellaneous Highlights: O'Dowd chopped Starc on to his own stumps
Netherlands final five batters fell for just six runs
